This paper is about using neural networks to approximate continuous functions, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithmic approach to finding the weights/parameters of the network, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks for artificial intelligence applications (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for signal processing and reconstruction, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
